# REAL Web Search Configuration
# Add ONE or more of these API keys to enable web search functionality
# The system will automatically use the first available provider

# =============================================================================
# RECOMMENDED: Serper.dev (Best Free Option)
# =============================================================================
# Sign up at: https://serper.dev
# Free tier: 1000 searches/month
# Features: Real Google search results, fast, reliable
VITE_SERPER_API_KEY=your_serper_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# ALTERNATIVE: SerpAPI (Good Free Option)
# =============================================================================
# Sign up at: https://serpapi.com
# Free tier: 100 searches/month
# Features: Google search results, good documentation
# VITE_SERPAPI_KEY=your_serpapi_key_here

# =============================================================================
# ENTERPRISE: Bing Web Search API
# =============================================================================
# Sign up at: https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/services/cognitive-services/bing-web-search-api/
# Features: Microsoft's search API, commercial grade
# VITE_BING_SEARCH_API_KEY=your_bing_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# PRIVACY-FOCUSED: Brave Search API
# =============================================================================
# Sign up at: https://brave.com/search/api/
# Features: Privacy-focused search, no tracking
# VITE_BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY=your_brave_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Choose a provider (Serper.dev recommended for beginners)
# 2. Sign up and get your API key
# 3. Copy this file to .env.local
# 4. Add your API key above
# 5. Restart your development server
# 6. Test the web search in the AI assistant

# =============================================================================
# FALLBACK BEHAVIOR
# =============================================================================
# If no API keys are configured, the system will:
# - Use local knowledge base only
# - Provide structured fallback responses for common tech queries
# - Show helpful error messages guiding users to web resources
# 
# The AI assistant will always work, with or without web search APIs!

# =============================================================================
# API KEY PRIORITY (uses first available)
# =============================================================================
# 1. Serper.dev (VITE_SERPER_API_KEY)
# 2. SerpAPI (VITE_SERPAPI_KEY) 
# 3. Brave Search (VITE_BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY)
# 4. Bing Search (VITE_BING_SEARCH_API_KEY)
# 5. Fallback system (always available)

# =============================================================================
# COST COMPARISON (as of 2024)
# =============================================================================
# Serper.dev:      1000 free searches/month, then $5/1000 searches
# SerpAPI:         100 free searches/month, then $50/5000 searches  
# Bing Search:     1000 free searches/month, then $4/1000 searches
# Brave Search:    Contact for pricing (privacy-focused)
# 
# For most portfolios, the free tiers are more than sufficient!
